         <div type="edition" xml:lang="kaw-Latn" rendition="class:38769 maturity:83213">
<lg n="1" met="sragdharā" xml:lang="san-Latn">
<l n="a">(1) ++++-++[amita-va]la-mahā-vajra-paryyaṅka-vaddhaḥ </l>
<l n="b">rakṣatv āmūla-siṅho bhavaja-bhavacarātyanta-saṁkru(2)-+= |</l>
<l n="c">++++-++--matara-hitottuṅga-śaila-stha-śūro </l>
<l n="d">yat saj-jīvāpara-smāra-valam akhila+(3)+-++-+= ||</l>
<!-- 	b. -siṅho: ṣimho C. -->
</lg>
<lg n="2" met="sragdharā" xml:lang="san-Latn">
<l n="a">++++-++-vara-vaśa-vatāsāditādharmma-vr̥ndān·</l>
<l n="b">lokānāṁ laukya-vuddhair agaditam atu(4)[la]+-++-+= | </l>
<l n="c">++++-++cchidam akhila-bhava-vyādhi-bhaiṣajyam agraṁ</l>
<l n="d">sad-dharmaṁ yukti-cittaḥ praṇama(5)[ti] --++-++-+= ||</l>
</lg>
<lg n="3" met="sragdharā" xml:lang="san-Latn">
<l n="a">++t kāruṇyam agrañ jagati gati-śatānanta-duḥkhābhibhūte</l>
<l n="b">bhakti-svīyā - (6) ++------++-++-mānām· |</l>
<l n="c">prītyā rājā tale danda-dhara-tula-mahājñāna-puṇya-prasūti-</l>
<l n="d">(7) ++++-++------++-tām vandya-vandyaḥ ||</l>
<!-- 	a. maybe -bhūtaiḥ?
	c. danda- norm. daṇḍa-.
 -->
</lg>
<lg n="4" met="vasantatilakā" xml:lang="san-Latn">
<l n="a">śrīmat-samasta-sugatais sasutaiḥ parāntyaiḥ</l> 
<l n="b">nīrukta(8)+---+--+-+= |</l>
<l n="c">++-+tsu taruṇām atha duḥkhiteṣu</l> 
<l n="d">satveṣu vuddha-cariteṣu garīyasīñ ca ||</l>
<!-- 	b. nirukta: is this expected parsing possible?
	d. satveṣu: norm. sattveṣu.
 -->
</lg>
<lg n="5" met="vasantatilakā" xml:lang="san-Latn">
<l n="a">śraddhāñ ca (9) +---+--+-+=</l>
<l n="b">[tan-maṇḍa]lāgra-guṇavad-gaṇam atyavāśi |</l>
<l n="c">lebhe vigūḍha-manujendra-gaṇān mahiṣyam· <space/></l>
<l n="d">śai(10)[lendra-vaṁśatilaka] --+-+= ||</l>
<!-- 	c. vigūḍha-: Long 2014: 187 n. 39: « Damais (1955: 43, n. 1) expressed strong doubt about de Casparis’ reading  vigūḍha ... noting that the -ḍha appears to be a -gha. » Read vidhūya? Or vibhūya? Bosch (1952: 197, n. 12) suggests aviguṇān, but this would be unmetrical.
 -->
</lg>
<lg n="6" met="vasantatilakā" xml:lang="san-Latn">
<l n="a">vistīrṇṇa-saṅga --+ pyananāmvu-pūrṇṇa-</l>
<l n="b">prauḍha-dviṣad-vikasitāmvuja-locanāni |</l>
<l n="c">(11) tan-maṇḍalāgra--+--+-+=</l>
<l n="d">nitya-smr̥tāni sahasaiva samākucanti ||</l>
<!-- 	a. vistīrṇṇa-: stīr	
	c.  tan-maṇḍalāgra-:  tan-maṇḍalā- C. The akṣaera gra is visible on the Leiden plastercast. Cf. also st. V, pāda b.
	d. nitya-: nītya- C. Probably a printing error.
 -->
</lg>
<lg n="7" met="vasantatilakā" xml:lang="san-Latn">
<l n="a">caṇḍa-pratāpa-paritāpita-bhūri-bhū(12)paḥ</l>
<l n="b">santāpa-pāvanam a +--+-+= |</l>
<l n="c">++guṇo ’pi hira-pīta-karo ’vadātaḥ</l> 
<l n="d">sācātirānubhava-toṣa-vivi(13)kta-cittaḥ ||</l>
<!-- 	b. pāvanam a +: could be pāvana-saṅga-? Sarkar proposes -pāvana-matiḥ
	c. ++guṇo: LC seems to have proposed śūro guṇo to Long.
	d. sācātirānubhava-: Āvodhananānubhava?
 -->
</lg>
<lg n="8" met="vasantatilakā" xml:lang="san-Latn">
<l n="a">śrīmān asau samaratuṅga Iti kṣitī[ndraḥ]</l>
<l n="b">++-+-śavidhām adharo mahīyān· | </l>
<l n="c">tasyātivallabhatarā (14) duhiteha cakre</l>
<l n="d">grāme jinālayam araṁ --+-+= ||</l>
<!-- 	b. ++-+-śavidhām adharo mahīyān: de Casparis, Pras. Indo. I, p. 177, reconstructs bhūmim vyadhād daśavidhām adharo mahīyān. But the estampage seems to show mahyīyān·.
 -->
</lg>
<lg n="9" met="vasantatilakā" xml:lang="san-Latn">
<l n="a">++mi-bhūpa-guṇa-śīla-vibhūṣanākhyā</l>
<l n="b">strai(15)ṇāgamāvirahitā karuṇātmikā ca | </l>
<l n="c">rārajyate na - titārya -+-+=</l>
<l n="d">++-rānta-viśayeṣu karo(16)ti bhaktim· ||</l>
<!-- 	a. ++mi: Sarkar proposes to restore sāsvāmi-.
	a. - -vibhūṣanākhyā C. Read -vibhūṣanāḍhyā?
	b. strai(15)ṇāgamā: or straiṇāgaṇā?
	c. - titārya: LC has proposed [pa]titārya
	d. ++- -rānta: C (1950: 43) proposes [utta]rānta-.
	d. norm. viṣayeṣu?
 -->
</lg>
<lg n="10" met="gīti" xml:lang="san-Latn"><!-- metrical problem -->
<l n="ab">sā kāntiñ candramaso gatiñ ca haṅsāt svarañ ca kalaviṅkāt· </l>
<l n="cd">se ===+ ṇāṁ hara(17)ti śrīmat-pramodavarddhanī khyātā ||</l>
<!-- 	cd. se = : sage? sabhe? sago? sabho?
	cd. pramoda-: prāmoda- C. See Damais (1968: 327) Nous ne savons pourquoi De C. transcrit (p. 37, ligne 5 et passim) le nom de la Princesse « Prâmodawardhanï » alors que l'inscription a nettement prâmodawarddhan{ l) avec une brève (1). A la note 5 de la p. 46, il déclare : « On se serait attendu à Prâmodya (qui augmente la joie); ... ». Pourquoi s'attendre à un autre mot que celui qui se trouve dans l'inscription, prâmoda, qui est bien connu en sanskrit (2)?
	Metrical problem En fait, il doit y avoir 30 morae à chaque vers. Mais si sa transcription peut bien donner ce total pour le second vers, c'est parce qu'il interprète prâmoda° alors que l'inscription a prâ°.
 -->
</lg>
<lg n="11" met="śārdūlavikrīḍita" xml:lang="san-Latn">
<l n="a">śākaindryāṁ rasa-sāgara-kṣitidharair yyāntyāṁ sa mā[se śucau]</l>
<l n="b">+++-(18) ca rāma-pakṣa-vasato kāṣṭā-tithau tatra ca</l>
<l n="c">tuṁlai-nāma-Umānis-ākhya-sahite vāre purāṇād gu[rau]</l>
<l n="d">+(19)pte śrī-ghananātham āryya-sahitaṁ prātiṣṭhipan mandire ||</l>
<!-- 
	See Damais 1955: 114–155, n. 2.
	c. purāṇād: can we read purāṇaṅ?
 -->
</lg>
<lg n="12" met="vasantatilakā" xml:lang="san-Latn">
<l n="a">tacchendu-vimva-śakala-pratimaṁ vibhāti </l>
<l n="b">rāhor bhiyā sapa(20)di sampatitaṁ dharitryāṁ</l>
<l n="c">tasyānuguṇyam athavedam udeti śubhraḥ</l>
<l n="d">vuddhais sakr̥tyataruṇair uṣitaṁ manojña(21)m· ||</l>
<!-- 	a. tac cendu-vimva-sakala-?
	c. tasyānuguṇyam: tasyānupuṇyam C.
	c. athavedam: thus Bosch (1952: 194); atha vedim C.
	c. śubhraḥ: bhūbhr̥t· C.
	d. vuddhais: vr̥ddhais C. -->
</lg>
<lg n="13" met="anuṣṭubh" xml:lang="san-Latn">
<l n="a">śrīmad-veṇuvanābhikhyam</l> 
<l n="b">vidhāya jina-mandiraṁ</l>
<l n="c">yat puṇyam āptam etena</l> 
<l n="d">daśadāpnotu saugatam· ||</l>
<!-- 	a. -khyam: it seems that the plaster cast shows -khyām.
 -->
</lg>
<lg n="14" met="anuṣṭubh" xml:lang="san-Latn">
<l n="a">pa(22)dam atyanta-duṣprāpam</l> 
<l n="b">anuttaram agocaraṁ</l>
<l n="c">tat-sutānāṁ mayā yuktaṁ</l> 
<l n="d">tūrṇṇam eva labheya yat· ||</l>
<!-- 	c. tat-sutānāṁ:? tat sutarāṁ?
	d. labheya: labbeya C (misprint).
 -->
</lg>
<lg n="15" met="sragdharā" xml:lang="san-Latn">
<l n="a">Aurvvāgnir yā[va](23)d uṣṇa-śvasana-vaśa-gatākṣanyadam bodhi-dr̥ṣṭyā</l>
<l n="b">yāvat prāntā dharitrī vivudha-gaṇa-samākrānta-mūrttiś ca meruḥ</l>
<l n="c">yāva[t khe] (24) svān gabhastīn daśa-śata-gaṇanām ujjhati vyoma-cakre</l>
<l n="d">++++-++sugata-guṇa-gaṇas tāvad āstām vihāraḥ ||</l>
<!-- 	b. prāntā: prānto? prāptā?
	c. -cakre: -vr̥traḥ C.
	d.  śrī
 -->
</lg>
<p>

</p>
